 
 In order to boot on older computers with floppy disks, here is an image with the GRUB boot loader version 1.
 Also You can write image on USB stick well for newer computers.

 1. Uncompress grub1.img.tar.xz
 2. Write (raw, with dd cmd on UNIX) grub1.img on floppy or USB stick.
 3. Mount floppy or USB stick media on computer.
 4. From img/ folder copy files ( load, core, devs, libs, usrs, gdt_, apps ) to mounted media into boot/ folder.

 Now the media is prepared for booting on real machine or emulators.
